# udev rule: Trigger camera sync service when a USB camera is connected.
#
# HOW TO FIND YOUR CAMERA'S USB IDs:
#   1. Plug in your camera via USB
#   2. Run: lsusb | grep -i canon    (or replace "canon" with your camera brand)
#   3. Output example: Bus 001 Device 015: ID 04a9:32f9 Canon, Inc. Canon Digital Camera
#      - "04a9" is the vendor ID  (04a9 = Canon; all Canon cameras share this)
#      - "32f9" is the product ID (specific to Canon EOS M50 Mark II)
#
# COMMON CANON PRODUCT IDs (for reference):
#   04a9:32f9  Canon EOS M50 Mark II
#   04a9:32d2  Canon EOS R
#   04a9:32da  Canon EOS RP
#   04a9:32e2  Canon EOS R5
#   04a9:32e4  Canon EOS R6
#
# TO ADAPT FOR YOUR CAMERA:
#   - Change ATTR{idProduct} to match your camera's product ID from lsusb
#   - If using a non-Canon camera, also change ATTR{idVendor} (e.g., Nikon = 04b0, Sony = 054c)
#
# NOTE: This file is auto-generated by install.sh from config.yml.
#       To change values, edit config.yml and re-run: sudo ./install.sh

ACTION=="add", SUBSYSTEM=="usb", ATTR{idVendor}=="04a9", ATTR{idProduct}=="32f9", MODE="0660", GROUP="plugdev", TAG+="systemd", ENV{SYSTEMD_WANTS}="canon-camera-sync.service"
